			<ns0:name>pol...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101953680983947802512/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Each tester has to define its own version of PPP, PPP_Instance and PPP_Class_Deprecated interfaces to turn each test into a scriptable PPAPI plugin. In addition, s/he needs to script the web page to report invoked callbacks.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
A lot of duplication. A lot of code to handle. A lot of code to update when things change.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Factor out common code into a template library and provide a registration mechanism for each test case.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Existing tests are ported to the new harness. They are passing.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
More tests written faster.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-07-15T07:50:08.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-04-14T07:51:48.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
